Habitual Alberta resident - refers to patients who belong to the province of Alberta;
Plagued by Diabetes - refers to patients with a confirmed comorbidity of 'Diabetes';
Diagnosed in the year 2023 - refers to cases that were confirmed between '2023-01-01' and '2023-12-31';
At least six such cases - refers to the condition that the count of report IDs should be greater than 5.

Confirmed cases refer to cases with a status description of 'confirmed' in the case_status table; 
Transmission types are categories that describe how a case was transmitted, such as community or travel-related;
A rank is assigned to each province based on the total number of cases in descending order for each transmission type.
